# Git push and deploy — user approval required

This project is tested **locally** (`npm run dev` at http://localhost:3000) before anything goes to production.

## Never do without explicit user request

- `git push` (any remote or branch)
- `git push -u origin …`
- Force push
- Creating/updating a PR that pushes commits
- Triggering Vercel/production deploys

## Commits

- Do **not** commit unless the user explicitly asks (same as global git safety rules).
- When asked to commit, still do **not** push unless they also ask to push.

## When the user is ready

Only push when they clearly say so, e.g.:

- "push to GitHub"
- "push this branch"
- "deploy to production"

Until then, finish work locally and tell them what to run or what changed — do not push on their behalf.

## Local testing reminder

After code changes, suggest verifying with:

```bash
npm run dev
```

Optional: `npm run typecheck` before they ask to push.
